{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"sxmu9ecyn89qo1xq6zvb3eq","title":"Mock Function","desc":"","updated":1658252546189,"created":1646427087594,"custom":{},"fname":"jest.mock-function","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"../main/tech","name":"tech"},"contentHash":"ba536559fc53d725eaa52a0af8000589","links":[],"anchors":{"remaking-jestfn":{"type":"header","text":"Remaking jest.fn","value":"remaking-jestfn","line":42,"column":0,"depth":3},"axios-example":{"type":"header","text":"Axios example","value":"axios-example","line":61,"column":0,"depth":3},"ue-resources":{"type":"header","text":"UE Resources","value":"ue-resources","line":73,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["ydz5o0y6rnq2cmzcxjlqv3i"],"parent":"LgW7mTIALODoXc54B3p6S","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"mock-function\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#mock-function\"></a>Mock Function</h1>\n<p>The reason why we mock is that we want to replace something we don't control  with something that we do control.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\"don't control\" can mean a third-party module, or even just a function/class that we wrote that we are using in the current unit we are testing.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Mock functions provide benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>allows us to test the links between different units by erasing implementation details of a function</li>\n<li>allows us to peek into the mock (via the <code>.mock</code> property), giving us valuable information on it like, \n<ul>\n<li>it was called or not </li>\n<li>which parameters were passed to it</li>\n<li>what the return value was</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>allows us to change the implementation of the original function</li>\n<li>allows us to set return values</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We can create mock functions in 2 different ways:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>creating a mock function to use in test code</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li><code>jest.mock</code> - mock an entire module (e.g. axios)</li>\n<li><code>jest.fn</code></li>\n<li><code>jest.spyOn</code></li>\n</ul>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>writing a <a href=\"https://jestjs.io/docs/manual-mocks\">manual mock</a> to override a module dependency</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li>involves making a <code>__mocks__</code> directory</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Mock functions return undefined by default, but we can inject return values into it:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> myMock <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> jest<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">fn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token console class-name\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token function\">myMock</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// > undefined</span>\n\nmyMock<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">mockReturnValueOnce</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">mockReturnValueOnce</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'x'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">mockReturnValue</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token console class-name\">console</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token function\">myMock</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token function\">myMock</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token function\">myMock</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token function\">myMock</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// > 10, 'x', true, true</span>\n</code></pre>\n<p>In order to mock properly, Jest needs <code>jest.mock('moduleName')</code> to be in the same scope as the import statement (ie. top level).</p>\n<h3 id=\"remaking-jestfn\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#remaking-jestfn\"></a>Remaking <code>jest.fn</code></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.pluralsight.com/guides/how-does-jest.fn()-work\">source</a></li>\n</ul>\n<pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token comment\">// 1. The mock function factory</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">fn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">implementation</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// 2. The mock function</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">mockFn</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\"><span class=\"token spread operator\">...</span>args</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// 4. Store the arguments used</span>\n    mockFn<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token property-access\">mock</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token property-access\">calls</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">push</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>args<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword control-flow\">return</span> <span class=\"token function\">implementation</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token spread operator\">...</span>args<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// call the implementation</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// 3. Mock state</span>\n  mockFn<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token property-access\">mock</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">calls</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword control-flow\">return</span> mockFn<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"axios-example\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#axios-example\"></a>Axios example</h3>\n<p>Imagine we are testing a module (<code>Users</code>) which internally calls <code>axios.get</code>: </p>\n<pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Users</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">static</span> <span class=\"token function\">all</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword control-flow\">return</span> axios<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">get</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'/users.json'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">resp</span> <span class=\"token arrow operator\">=></span> resp<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token property-access\">data</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Of course, we don't want our <code>Users.test.js</code> unit test to actually make a GET request. Therefore, we need to mock it with <code>jest.mock</code></p>\n<h2 id=\"ue-resources\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#ue-resources\"></a>UE Resources</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.pluralsight.com/guides/how-does-jest.fn()-work\">https://www.pluralsight.com/guides/how-does-jest.fn()-work</a></p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/ydz5o0y6rnq2cmzcxjlqv3i\">API</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"olZIVfSs2uLLr3BppFh4K","title":"Digital Garden","desc":"","updated":1645685923101,"created":1615482407722,"custom":{"nav_order"